# Full Feature Implementation Plan

## Goal
Fix all bugs, wire up admin product creation & order management, complete the user purchase flow (choose â†’ cart â†’ checkout â†’ order confirmation), and ensure emails are sent to both user and admin on order placement.

---

## Bugs Found & Fixes

### Bug 1 â€“ Missing EMAIL credentials in .env
The [sendEmail.js](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/utils/sendEmail.js) uses `EMAIL_USER` and `EMAIL_PASS` env vars, but the [.env](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/.env) file has no email credentials. The backend must have these to send transactional emails.

**Fix:** Add `EMAIL_USER` and `EMAIL_PASS` to [backend/.env](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/.env).

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The user must provide their Gmail credentials. We'll use the existing `ADMIN_EMAIL` value as the email user and `ADMIN_PASSWORD` as the app password.

### Bug 2 â€“ Admin Dashboard stats missing `processingOrders` / `shippedOrders`
`adminController.getDashboardStats` returns `orderStatusDistribution` but only maps `Pending`, `Delivered`, `Cancelled` into `overview`. The frontend [AdminDashboard.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/admin/AdminDashboard.tsx) also expects `processingOrders` and `shippedOrders`, but they're absent in the response.

**Fix:** Add `processingOrders` and `shippingOrders` to the stats overview in [adminController.js](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/controllers/adminController.js).

### Bug 3 â€“ Missing route `/order-confirmation/:id` 
[Checkout.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/Checkout.tsx) navigates to `/order-confirmation/${data._id}`, but `/order-confirmation/:id` is not in [App.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/App.tsx). Only `/orders/:id` exists (which loads [OrderConfirmation](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/utils/sendEmail.js#92-204)).

**Fix:** Add the `/order-confirmation/:id` route in [App.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/App.tsx) pointing to [OrderConfirmation](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/utils/sendEmail.js#92-204).

### Bug 4 â€“ [AddProduct.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/admin/AddProduct.tsx) sends to wrong API endpoint
The [AddProduct.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/admin/AddProduct.tsx) admin page (22KB) likely sends JSON to `/api/products` instead of the correct `/api/admin/products` with multipart form data for image upload. 

**Fix:** Rewrite [AddProduct.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/admin/AddProduct.tsx) to use the correct `/api/admin/products` endpoint with `FormData` for image upload.

### Bug 5 â€“ Admin user's `role` check in auth â€” login works but redirect logic
The [Auth.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/pages/Auth.tsx) redirects admins to `/admin` after login based on `res.user?.role`. The [login](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/context/StoreContext.tsx#83-103) function in [StoreContext.tsx](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/frontend/context/StoreContext.tsx) sets `user` to `data` (which includes `role`), and returns `{ success: true, user: data }`. This should work. Need to verify the admin user actually exists in the database. 

**Fix:** Ensure the admin user is seeded with `npm run seed`.

### Bug 6 â€“ [deleteProduct](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/controllers/productController.js#180-197) uses deprecated `.remove()` in controllers
[productController.js](file:///d:/WEB%20Dev/Saree%20Shop/Final%20Project/backend/src/controllers/productController.js) calls `product.remove()` which is removed in Mongoose 7+.

**Fix:** Change to `product.deleteOne()`.

